            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here are the latest updates for the London Underground as of December 2025:\n\n1. **General Service Status**:\n   - Most lines are reporting good service, but there are some planned maintenance works affecting service on specific lines.\n\n2. **Current Disruptions**:\n   - **Metropolitan Line**: Part closure between Harrow-on-the-Hill and Uxbridge on December 6-7. Replacement bus service available [Traffic Delays](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/).\n   - **Northern Line**: Partial closures with no service between Charing Cross and Golders Green / High Barnet overnight on December 6-7. Replacement buses are available [Traffic Delays](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/).\n   - **Piccadilly Line**: No service between Acton Town and Uxbridge on December 6-7; replacement bus service in place [Traffic Delays](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/).\n\n3. **Planned Works**:\n   - Several lines have planned closures for maintenance and upgrade works, especially during weekends. Keep this in mind while planning travel.\n\n4. **Christmas and New Year Schedule**:\n   - TfL has confirmed no services on Christmas Day.\n   - Early finishes on Christmas Eve.\n   - Overnight services on New Year’s Eve, but expect some stations to close sporadically due to crowd control measures [TfL](https://tfl.gov.uk/status-updates/major-works-and-events/christmas-and-new-year-travel).\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's best to check the [TfL website](https://tfl.gov.uk) or use the TfL Go app before you travel.",
